<p>In 2017, Xia et al. [
 <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR52">52</xref>] proposed a very simple novel method by which even non-experts can estimate HIV incidence using HIV case reporting data. The method assumes that HIV incidence and case finding are stable within each 3-year period. The timeframe of interest is broken down into overlapping 3-year periods (e.g., 2002−2004,2003−2005,⋯,2008−2010). The HIV incidence for the second year of each 3-year period can be estimated by solving the following equations: 
 <disp-formula id="Equn">
  <alternatives>
   <tex-math id="M65">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document} $$R=\frac{D_{1}}{U_{1}+I_{1}}=\frac{D_{2}}{U_{2}+I_{2}}=\frac{D_{3}}{U_{3}+I_{3}},$$ \end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M66">
    <mrow>
     <mi>R</mi>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mfrac>
      <mrow>
       <msub>
        <mrow>
         <mi>D</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mrow>
         <mn>1</mn>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
      <mrow>
       <msub>
        <mrow>
         <mi>U</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mrow>
         <mn>1</mn>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
       <mo>+</mo>
       <msub>
        <mrow>
         <mi>I</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mrow>
         <mn>1</mn>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
     </mfrac>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mfrac>
      <mrow>
       <msub>
        <mrow>
         <mi>D</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mrow>
         <mn>2</mn>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
      <mrow>
       <msub>
        <mrow>
         <mi>U</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mrow>
         <mn>2</mn>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
       <mo>+</mo>
       <msub>
        <mrow>
         <mi>I</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mrow>
         <mn>2</mn>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
     </mfrac>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mfrac>
      <mrow>
       <msub>
        <mrow>
         <mi>D</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mrow>
         <mn>3</mn>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
      <mrow>
       <msub>
        <mrow>
         <mi>U</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mrow>
         <mn>3</mn>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
       <mo>+</mo>
       <msub>
        <mrow>
         <mi>I</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mrow>
         <mn>3</mn>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
     </mfrac>
     <mo>,</mo>
    </mrow>
   </math>
   <graphic xlink:href="12976_2019_118_Article_Equn.gif" position="anchor" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </disp-formula> and 
