 <italic>R</italic> is the case finding rate in a year, 
 <italic>D</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>i</italic>
 </sub> is the number of new diagnoses in year 
 <italic>i</italic>, 
 <italic>U</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>i</italic>
 </sub> is the number of undiagnosed cases at the beginning of year 
 <italic>i</italic>, and 
 <italic>I</italic>
 <sub>1</sub> is the HIV incidence in year 
 <italic>i</italic> (
 <italic>i</italic>=1,2,3). Then, 
 <disp-formula id="Equs">
  <alternatives>
   <tex-math id="M75">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document} $$I_{2}\approx\frac{D_{1}D_{3}-D_{2}D_{2}}{D_{1}-2D_{2}+D_{3}}.$$ \end{document}</tex-math>
